The paper discusses a variant of the Adam algorithm for large-scale machine learning, which is a topic closely related to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the performance of the algorithm for strongly convex functions, which is a topic related to optimization (cs.NE) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper provides empirical results on training deep networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
